race.comment: This is tricky. VIVA MARCONI (1) peaks off narrow defeats at York and Geraldton. Draws inside and is capable of leading should connections desire. Has a 3kg claim and that brings him right into it. KAT FIVE (10) resumed here over 1200m with a 3L defeat. Will be fitter and the extra metres suit. She can make the finish today. WARDIKCAR (4) debuts and the in-form Galati sticks from a recent Lark Hill trial win. Has an awkward gate but on what we've seen he's capable of featuring. RACY RASCAL (7) started a $3.20 favourite at Narrogin on debut but offered little (vet cleared). He's obviously better than that and Chris Parnham is a key jockey engagement. Has the 2 gate and will get every chance to make amends.
